(firstQuint)Evaluation of the Efficacy of Cesamet for the Treatment of Pain in Patients With Multiple Sclerosis.

 The purpose of this study is to determine the safety and efficacy of Cesamet cent in the symptomatic treatment of pain due to Multiple Sclerosis.

 This is a phase IV, multi-center, open label outpatient clinical trial evaluating Cesamet cent treatment for control of pain due MS.

 The study has two phases: a Pretreatment Phase and a Treatment Phase.

